CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 21, 1955, eg. 9, reads: "This Week's Winner - We do not know what the churchgoer whose head is circles by Courier artist is looking at, but if she comes into the Courier office any time next week between Monday and Friday, 9 A. M. to 6 P. M., and identifies herself and the church she attended last Sunday, she will receive a five-dollar gift. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Women, men, and children standing on crowded sidewalk in front of Grace Memorial Presbyterian Church with car parked in street on left with licence plate "9391V," Bryn Mawr Road, Upper Hill District
